# casing rules

strategic lowercase is part of agency/42's visual identity. follow these rules for consistency.

## lowercase (always)

- navigation/menu items: `home`, `blog`, `archives`
- page titles: `blog`, `project archives`, `privacy policy`
- section headers: `our work`, `team`, `work with us`
- ui labels and ctas: `subscribe`, `watch â†’`, `back to blog`
- stats labels: `hours saved`, `annual value`, `months to roi`
- sidebar/meta labels: `on this page`
- client names: `agency/42`, `warner records`, `cogent world`
- product descriptions/subtext: `social agents that post, chat, and remember`

## title case (exceptions)

- article/blog titles: "The Cybernetic Organization"
- project names in archives: "Daybloom", "AI Training and Enablement", "LinkedIn MCP"
- featured product names on homepage: "Daybloom", "Miniverse"
- external content titles (videos, newsletters)
- legal document section headers: "1. Introduction"

## all caps

- redacted text: `[REDACTED]`

## as-is (never change)

- brand name: `Agency/42` (capital A, slash, capital number)
- proper names (people): Kenneth, Rob
